  "instructions": [
    "Combine ground nut oil, render-fat, and sesame oil in a saucepan over low heat.",
    "Add the bao mix and stir until combined.",
    "Gradually add water while stirring to form a dough.",
    "Knead the dough for 10 minutes until smooth.",
    "Let dough rest for 1 hour.",
    "Roll out dough to 1/4 inch thickness.",
    "Cut into small circles using a cookie cutter or the rim of a glass.",
    "Brush edges with sesame oil.",
    "Place a tablespoon of scallion oil and a pinch of sugar in the center of each circle.",
    "Fold dough over to form a half-moon shape and press edges to seal.",
    "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat.",
    "Cook bao for 2-3 minutes on each side until golden brown.",
    "Serve warm with soy sauce and scallions."
